Provenance notes (not third-party code)
================================================================================

- `CheckCapacity` (pallets/microblog/src/lib.rs) is an ORIGINAL implementation of
  a standard lazy token-bucket rate limiter, written from this project's own
  economic specification (docs/ECONOMICS.md) and built entirely around this
  project's storage (`AllowedStake`, `Capacity`, `metered_cost`, `ForeignCost`).
  It contains no third-party rate-limiting code and carries no external license
  obligation. (An early planning note that speculated a GPL-3.0 derivation was
  never reflected in the shipped code.)

================================================================================
Licensing of the distributed binaries
================================================================================

This project's own source is Apache-2.0. The artifacts it distributes are a
combined work that is not.

`pallet-skip-feeless-payment` (v23.0.0) is a direct dependency of the runtime.
The crate is published under `license = "GPL-3.0-only"` with NO Classpath
exception — unlike the `sc-*` client crates above, whose Classpath exception is
exactly what makes linking them from an Apache-2.0 binary fine. That pallet is
compiled into the runtime WASM, and the runtime WASM is embedded in the
chainspec this repo ships (`chainspecs/preprod.raw.json`), so the shipped
chainspec and the `cogno-chain-node` binary carry GPL-3.0-only code.

(The crate's own source headers say Apache-2.0, which contradicts its published
crate metadata. We take the published license at its word rather than assume the
looser reading.)

Practically: take the source under Apache-2.0; treat any binary or chainspec you
receive from us — and any you build with this dependency in place — as GPL-3.0.
Removing the dependency is being looked at; until it is gone, this is the honest
statement of where the project stands.
